Business Brief -- Secom General Corp.:
   Maker of Tools Seeks Talks
   About Purchasing Park-Ohio
Last spring, Park-Ohio, a maker of machinery, rubber and
plastic products, said that it "explored the possible sale of
the company," but that no deals were struck. Park-Ohio said
Secom hasn't submitted any proposals, but that it "will give
appropriate consideration to any specific bonafide
transaction they may propose."
   In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, Park-Ohio
rose 25 cents to $3.875.